http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/NDRF-conducts-mock-drill/article13983677.ece

Personnel from the National Disaster Response Force (NDRF) demonstrated various techniques to rescue people and render first aid to the needy in emergency situations such as natural disasters at an awareness programme on disaster management held in Bhadrachalam on Tuesday.According to sources, the demonstration was conducted as part of a community awareness programme by the NDRF personnel at the Government Degree College premises in the temple town.A large number of students from various educational institutions watched the mock drill conducted by the NDRF personnel on the occasion.Bhadrachalam Revenue Divisional Officer B Venkateshwarlu, NDRF team leader Vipin Singh, Bhadrachalam Station Fire Officer Suresh Kumar and others spoke.